<item>
            <title>[LU-8359] Wrong evict during failover</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8359</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;MRP-3604 ldlm: Wrong evict during failover&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is a race between setting obd_fail &amp;amp; OBD_OPT_FAILOVER.&lt;br/&gt;
tgt_client_del() checks only OBD_OPT_FAILOVER&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is better to rely only on obd_fail.&lt;br/&gt;
We shouldn&apos;t evict during failover at all, it should&lt;br/&gt;
be handled on a new server.&lt;br/&gt;
Such wrong evict can happen when server can&apos;t send CP AST&lt;br/&gt;
to the client because failover has started already.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
